akka.stream.impl

Class StreamLayout.StructuralInfoModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • akka.stream.impl.StreamLayout.StructuralInfoModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StreamLayout.Module, java.io.Serializable, scala.Equals, scala.Product
    Enclosing class:
    StreamLayout

    public static final class StreamLayout.StructuralInfoModule
extends java.lang.Object
implements StreamLayout.Module, scala.Product, scala.Serializable
    INTERNAL API

    When fusing a Graph a part of the internal stage wirings are hidden within akka.stream.impl.fusing.GraphInterpreter#GraphAssembly objects that are optimized for high-speed execution. This structural information module contains the wirings in a more accessible form, allowing traversal from port to upstream or downstream port and from there to the owning module (or graph vertex).

      • replaceShape

        public StreamLayout.Module replaceShape(Shape s)
        Description copied from interface: StreamLayout.Module
        Verify that the given Shape has the same ports and return a new module with that shape. Concrete implementations may throw UnsupportedOperationException where applicable.

        Please note that this method MUST NOT be implemented using a CopiedModule since the purpose of replaceShape can also be to rearrange the ports (as in BidiFlow.reversed) and that purpose would be defeated.

      • carbonCopy

        public StreamLayout.Module carbonCopy()
        Description copied from interface: StreamLayout.Module
        The purpose of this method is to create a copy to be included in a larger graph such that port identity clashes are avoided. Where a full copy is not possible or desirable, use a CopiedModule. The shape of the resulting module MUST NOT contain the same ports as this module&rsquo;s shape.
